oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: J.J. Savage store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of several people on the porch and in front of a store owned by Jesse Joshua "J.J." Savage (1871- 1937) near Catheys Creek in Hampshire. Some ride horses and mule-drawn wagons. A sign above the doorway reads: "Peter's Shoes sold by J.J. Savage."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: People; Children; Stores & shops; Mules; Carts & wagons; Horses
